HEADWORD: Euonymus
<hw>Eu*on"y*mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. (cf. L.
<ets>euonymos</ets>). fr. Gr. <?/, lit., of good name.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of small European and American trees; the
spindle tree. The bark is used as a cathartic.</def>⟦br⟧
